<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-08 08:07:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 'Star Wars' Tops $250 Million Mark / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The Jedi Knights might be unbeatable in  
theaters now, but they could face their first real competition this 
weekend, when retro-secret agent ``Austin Powers'' swaggers into 
theaters. 
</P>
<P>
	On the last weekend it enjoyed the young male audience all to  
itself, ``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace'' grossed $32.9 
million, topping $250 million in just three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	The ``Star Wars'' prequel has so far earned $255.8 million at  
North American theaters. 
</P>
<P>
	But the ``Austin Powers'' sequel, the first movie considered any  
real match for the Force, opens Friday. Studios had steered clear 
of the space blockbuster or counter-programmed with romances and 
art films. 
</P>
<P>
	One of those alternatives, the romantic comedy ``Notting Hill,''  
with Julia Roberts and Hugh Grant, collected $15 million in its 
second week against ``The Phantom Menace.'' It finished second. 
</P>
<P>
	The man-who-lived-with-gorillas movie, ``Instinct,'' starring  
Anthony Hopkins and Cuba Gooding Jr., opened to a so-so $10.4 
million for third place. 
</P>
<P>
	``The Mummy'' was fourth with $7.4 million, followed by  
``Entrapment,'' with $3.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The top 20 movies at North American theaters Friday through  
Sunday, followed by distributing studio, gross, number of theater 
locations, average receipts per location, total gross and number of 
weeks in release, as compiled Monday by Exhibitor Relations Co. 
Inc. and ACNielsen EDI Inc.: 
</P>
<P>
	1. ``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace,'' 20th Century  
Fox, $32.9 million, 3,023 locations, $10,880 average, $255.8 
million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	2. ``Notting Hill,'' Universal, $15 million, 2,752 locations,  
$5,455 average, $49.4 million, two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
