<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Versace: Profits Fall Due to Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILAN, Italy (AP) -- Italian fashion house Gianni Versace SpA  
said Tuesday that 1998 net profit fell 81 percent largely due to 
the Asian economic crisis, which cost it customers. 
</P>
<P>
	Profit was down to 16.5 billion lire (about $8.7 million) from  
87 billion lire ($46 million) a year earlier, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
	Chairman Santo Versace shot down speculation his group is  
seeking an alliance with another fashion group or a new financial 
partner. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're not thinking of any partner,'' Versace told journalists.  
</P>
<P>
	He declined to comment, however, on reports the group is close  
to selling the lease to its flagship store in Milan to LVMH Moet 
Hennessy Louis Vuitton, the large French luxury goods group 
currently battling for control of Gucci NV. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
