<HEADLINE> 2 Calif. Teen-Age Girls Shot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LYNWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Two teen-age cousins were shot to death  
by a young man as they walked to school today. 
</P>
<P>
	Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies were looking for a man  
described as being in his 20s. 
</P>
<P>
	Olivia Munguia, 17, and Jessica Yvette Zavala, 15, were shot  
numerous times about 7:45 a.m. as they walked to Lynwood High 
School, about 10 miles from downtown Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	Relatives of the teens said Munguia's ex-boyfriend was upset  
about being barred from Zavala's weekend birthday party. The former 
boyfriend called, using profanity and told Munguia, ``it's not 
over,'' Albert Ontiveros, a cousin, told KNBC-TV. 
</P>
<P>
	Los Angeles County sheriff's Deputy Joan Raber could not confirm  
details of the phone call. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
