<HEADLINE> Brazil 3, Netherlands 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GOIANIA, Brazil (AP) -- Leonardo scored twice during a  
three-minute span Tuesday, leading Brazil past the Netherlands 3-1 
in the teams' second exhibition game in four days. 
</P>
<P>
	After tying the Dutch 2-2 on Saturday, Brazil needed the victory  
to show a demanding Brazilian public that the national team under 
coach Wanderley Luxemburgo is force entering the Copa America 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	Amoroso opened the scoring for Brazil in the 22nd minute and  
Leonardo added goals in the 39th and 42nd minutes. The Dutch scored 
in the 80th minute on a free kick by Pierre Van Hooijdunk. 
  	   	
