<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Phillies Claim Telemaco on Waivers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- The Philadelphia Phillies claimed pitcher  
Amaury Telemaco on waivers from the Arizona Diamondbacks on 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The 25-year-old right-hander is expected to arrive at Veterans  
Stadium for Wednesday's game with the New York Yankees. Phillies 
manager Terry Francona said Telemaco would pitch out of the 
bullpen. 
</P>
<P>
	To make room for Telemaco on the team's 40-man roster, the  
Phillies transferred pitcher Matt Beech from the 15- to the 60-day 
disabled list. 
</P>
<P>
	Telemaco was 1-0 with a 7.50 ERA in five relief appearances with  
the Diamondbacks this season. He started the year on a minor-league 
rehab assignment due to tendinitis in his right shoulder. Overall 
in the majors, he is 13-20 in 81 appearances with a 4.81 ERA, 94 
walks and 173 strikeouts in 290 innings pitched. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
