<HEADLINE> 1 Dies in Maryland Walkway Collapse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARBUTUS, Md. (AP) -- A truck carrying a backhoe hit a pedestrian  
bridge and sent it crashing down on the Baltimore Beltway at the 
height of the today afternoon rush hour, killing one person and 
critically injuring three others. 
</P>
<P>
	The bridge crushed the front ends of three cars. The man who was  
killed was trapped in his sport utility vehicle, said Capt. Michael 
Robinson, a spokesman for the Baltimore County Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
	Three women were hospitalized in critical but stable condition.  
</P>
<P>
	There was no one on the footbridge, which has been closed for  
three years because of vandalism and crime. The bridge passed an 
inspection last month, said Jack Cahalan, a spokesman for the state 
Department of Transportation. 
</P>
<P>
	The accident halted traffic in both directions on Interstate 695  
-- the main artery around the city. 
</P>
<P>
	Police were questioning the truck driver.  
  	   	
</P>
