<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Stock Market 
and American Stock Exchange. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Unova Inc., down 1 1/2 at 12 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Unova expects to earn 6 cents a share in the second quarter,  
missing analysts' expectations by 8 cents a share. Unova, which 
makes industrial technology systems, said it is being hurt by costs 
at its Intermec Technologies unit. 

</P>
<P>
 *Toys R Us, down 1 3/4 at 22 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	The toy retailer may be hurt by a new competitor: the online  
baby store launched by rival eToys Inc. Toys R Us is in the process 
of creating an online subsidiary dubbed toysrus.com, which will 
also sell merchandise from Kids R Us and Babies R Us stores. 

</P>
<P>
 *Bank of New York Co., up 2 5/16 at 37    	
</P>
<P>
	The bank plans to sell BNY Financial Corp., its factoring and  
asset-based lending business, to General Motors Acceptance Corp. 
for $1.8 billion in cash. 

</P>
<P>
 *Johns Manville Corp., up 1/2 at 13 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Johns Manville will repurchase about $166.8 million common  
shares from its majority shareholder, Manville Personal Injury 
Settlement Trust, and will also prepay its $33.2 million debt to 
the trust. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Inprise Corp., up 1 3/8 at 5 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Microsoft Corp. will pay $100 million for the right to use  
Inprise's technology and to settle long-standing patent issues. 
Microsoft will also pay $25 million for 10 percent of Inprise's 
preferred shares. Inprise makes software-development tools. 

</P>
<P>
 *drkoop.com Inc., priced at 9, trading at 13 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	A Web site created by former U.S. Surgeon General Dr. C. Everett  
Koop made its initial public offering of stock. The company, which 
provides online health care information, was formerly known as 
Empower Health Corp. 

</P>
<P>
 *American Mobile Satellite Corp., up 4 3/8 at 21 1/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Southeastern Freight Lines Inc. will use American Mobile's  
satellite messaging technology in its fleet. American Mobile will 
equip more than 2,000 trucks within the next 18 months. 

</P>
<P>
 *Select Comfort Corp., down 6 at 7 1/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The maker of air beds may report a loss for the second quarter  
of 1999 and expects earnings for the period to be significantly 
below analysts' consensus estimates of 15 cents per share. 

</P>
<P>
 *Active Apparel Group Inc., up 1 11/32 at 4 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The company launched a store on Yahoo Inc.'s shopping Web site.  
Active Apparel will sell Everlast-brand men's and women's 
sportswear on the site. 

</P>
<P>
                               *AMEX    	

</P>
<P>
 *CVF Technologies, up 1 1/16 at 4    	
</P>
<P>
	CVF will form a business combination with USA Global Link Inc.,  
a privately held provider of telecommunications and electronic 
commerce services. CVF funds start-up companies, focusing primarily 
on electronic commerce. 


</P>
