<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Unusual Suspects Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WOLF CREEK, Ore. (AP) -- In a June 5 story about a pair of  
teen-age murder suspects in rural Oregon, The Associated Press 
erroneously attributed a passage that police found in the 
handwriting of suspect Josh Cain as being lyrics from Marilyn 
Manson's song ``Portrait of an American Family.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The passage is not from a Marilyn Manson song and prosecutors  
say they have not been able to identify its source. The passage 
was: ``Dealing with insanity, smoking pot, hating this (expletive) 
world, murder is the answer, I only kill to know I'm alive.'' 
  	   	
</P>
