<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Nortel To Combine Voice, Data, Video </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BRAMPTON, Ontario (AP) -- Nortel Networks Corp. today unveiled 11  
new products and enhancements to others in an effort to strengthen 
its position in the market for integrated data and voice networks. 
</P>
<P>
	The new products, available within a year, will help  
corporations combine voice and data traffic onto a single network, 
the Canadian company said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Nortel's new products range from the basic Inca Telecommuter,  
which allows a computer to be used as both a voice and data 
terminal over a single analog line, to the more sophisticated i3220 
Internet Phone, which will provide the front end for intelligent 
networks. 
</P>
<P>
	The company also announced that it is updating its CallPilot  
Unified Messaging System, which integrates a range of e-mail 
providers, including Microsoft Exchange, Outlook, Lotus Notes, 
Netscape Messenger and Eudora Pro. 
</P>
<P>
	Nortel is North America's second-largest maker of traditional  
phone equipment, behind Lucent Technologies. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
