<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Dead in Mass. Gas Station Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NORTH ANDOVER, Mass. (AP) -- A stolen car sped by a police car  
and smashed into a pickup truck in a gas station today, killing 
three young women in the car. 
</P>
<P>
	The car was going 75 mph in a 45 mph zone when it passed a  
parked police car, police said. The officer turned on his car's 
lights and pulled onto the highway to stop the car, which appeared 
to accelerate, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	When he next saw the Nissan Maxima, it had crashed into the gas  
station, striking some gas pumps and the truck. 
</P>
<P>
	A man in the car was hospitalized in critical condition. Another  
man, believed to be the driver, was arrested and faces charges of 
motor vehicle homicide and possession of a stolen car, authorities 
said. He was being treated for lesser injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	A man who was in or near the pickup truck was also hospitalized.  
His injuries were not believed to be life threatening. 
</P>
<P>
	The car was stolen in Manchester, N.H., on Saturday, police  
said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
