<HEADLINE> Robelot Leaving ``This Morning'' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Jane Robelot, a host of CBS's ``This Morning''  
since 1996, will leave following Friday's show, the network said. 
</P>
<P>
	Robelot will be replaced for a month by Thalia Assuras, who  
currently delivers news reports on CBS's morning show. 
</P>
<P>
	CBS announced last month that former ``Today'' host Bryant  
Gumbel will begin at ``This Morning'' in November. The network's 
morning show is perennially last in the ratings behind NBC's 
``Today'' and ABC's ``Good Morning America.'' 
</P>
<P>
	While CBS said it would launch a search for a Gumbel co-host,  
Robelot hasn't been mentioned as a possibility. Her current 
co-host, Mark McEwen, will stay on with Gumbel to deliver weather 
and entertainment reports. 
</P>
<P>
	CBS's Julie Chen will temporarily replace Assuras as host of the  
network's 5 a.m. news broadcast, the network said Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
