<HEADLINE> ABC Reveals Coll. Football Schedule </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- ABC released a schedule Tuesday that includes  
the Pigskin and Kickoff classics in August and the Sugar Bowl on 
Jan. 4, 2000, that will probably determine the national champion. 
</P>
<P>
	Arizona will begin the season at Penn State in the Pigskin  
Classic on Aug. 28. The following day, ABC will televise Miami-Ohio 
State in the Kickoff Classic at Giants Stadium in East Rutherford, 
N.J. 
</P>
<P>
	Games ABC will televise nationally include: Notre Dame at  
Michigan on Sept 4; Ohio State at Penn State on Oct. 16; Michigan 
at Penn State on Nov. 13; Ohio State at Michigan on Nov. 20; Texas 
at Texas A&AMP;M and Nebraska at Colorado on Nov. 26; and Notre Dame at 
Stanford on Nov. 27. 
</P>
<P>
	The network also will televise the Big 12 and SEC championship  
games on Dec. 3. 
</P>
<P>
	Among the bowl games on ABC are the Citrus, Rose and Orange on  
Jan. 1; the Fiesta on Jan. 2; and the Sugar on Jan. 4. 
</P>
<P>
	The Sugar Bowl matches the top two teams in the final Bowl  
Championship Series standings. 
</P>
<P>
	Regional telecasts include: UCLA at Ohio State and Georgia Tech  
at Florida State on Sept. 11; Miami at Florida State and Michigan 
at Michigan State on Oct. 9; and Georgia at Georgia Tech and 
Arizona at Arizona State on Nov. 27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
