<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mistrial in Fundraiser Tax Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The tax evasion trial of Democratic  
fund-raiser Maria S. Hsia ended in a mistrial after a jury said it 
was divided on all four counts but leaning toward acquittal. 
</P>
<P>
	The jury had reported it was unable to reach a verdict Friday,  
but U.S. District Judge Richard A. Paez told the panel to resume 
deliberations. Jurors again reported they were divided Monday, 
prompting the judge to declare a mistrial. 
</P>
<P>
	Federal prosecutors claim Hsia, who runs an immigration  
consulting business in San Marino, failed to file an income tax 
return for 1994, underestimated her income for 1995 and 1996 -- 
involving a total of $175,000 for the three years, and assisted in 
filing a false tax return for her business. 
</P>
<P>
	The tax charges are separate from accusations against Hsia in a  
Washington, D.C., case involving thousands of dollars Hsia is 
accused of funneling through Buddhist nuns at a 1996 Clinton-Gore 
campaign fund-raising event. Vice President Al Gore attended the 
event in Southern California. She is accused of soliciting illegal 
campaign contributions and arranging to use straw donors to hide 
the true source of the money. 
</P>
<P>
	Defense lawyer Kenneth Barish has said that he believes the tax  
charges in Los Angeles were intended to intimidate Hsia in the 
campaign finance case. 
</P>
<P>
	The judge gave federal prosecutors 10 days to decide whether to  
retry Hsia. 
</P>
<P>
	A message left Monday at the U.S. attorney's office in Los  
Angeles was not immediately returned. 
</P>
<P>
	Pending the prosecution's decision on whether to retry Hsia,  
Barish said he was preparing to file a motion to dismiss the case. 
</P>
<P>
	``She feels she's been vindicated. This is definitely a kind of  
a statement that she's on the right track. She's not guilty,'' 
Barish said. 
</P>
<P>
	If convicted, Hsia would face up to 10 years in prison and  
$850,000 in fines. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
