<HEADLINE> Dodgers Pitcher Suspended For Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Los Angeles pitcher Chan Ho Park was suspended  
for seven games and fined an undisclosed amount Tuesday for hitting 
and kicking Angels pitcher Tim Belcher during a game. 
</P>
<P>
	The fight last Saturday began after Belcher fielded Park's  
sacrifice bunt in the fifth inning and tagged him out. After a 
brief exchange of words, Park forearmed Belcher in the face and 
followed that up with a leaping kick. 
</P>
<P>
	Both benches and bullpens emptied, and Park was ejected. Matt  
Walbeck had hit a grand slam off Park an inning earlier. 
</P>
<P>
	Park, 4-3 with a 4.84 ERA in 12 starts this season, was to begin  
his suspension on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	There was no immediate word on whether he would appeal. If he  
does, the suspension would not start until after a hearing before 
NL president Leonard Coleman Jr. 
  	   	
</P>
