<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Tuesday on the New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Stock 
Market, and American Stock Exchange. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Unova Inc. fell 1 to 13 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Unova expects to earn 6 cents a share in the second quarter,  
missing analysts' expectations by 8 cents a share. Unova, which 
makes industrial technology systems, said it is being hurt by costs 
at its Intermec Technologies unit. 

</P>
<P>
 *Toys R Us fell 2 1/2 to 22    	
</P>
<P>
	The toy retailer may be hurt by a new competitor: the online  
baby store launched by rival eToys Inc. Toys R Us is in the process 
of creating an online subsidiary dubbed toysrus.com, which will 
also sell merchandise from Kids R Us and Babies R Us stores. 

</P>
<P>
 *Bank of New York Co. rose 2 3/8 to 37 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The bank plans to sell BNY Financial Corp., its factoring and  
asset-based lending business, to General Motors Acceptance Corp. 
for $1.8 billion in cash. 

</P>
