<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-08 05:40:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Agassi Has Pulled Thigh Muscle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HALLE, Germany (AP) -- Andre Agassi has a pulled muscle in his  
right thigh and is returning to the United States for treatment. 
</P>
<P>
	The injury today forced Agassi to withdraw from the Gerry Weber  
Open, a major ATP buildup on grass for Wimbledon. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a great disappointment for me,'' the newly crowned French  
Open champion said. ``I thought two days of rest would be enough.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``I'd already felt it after the third round in Paris. This  
morning I thought it was only a sore muscle but unfortunately it is 
not. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't want to take any risks. I want to play Wimbledon.''  
</P>
<P>
	Wimbledon starts June 28. Agassi won the British tournament in  
1992, his first Grand Slam title. 
</P>
<P>
	He added the U.S. Open in 1994 and the Australian Open in 1995.  
</P>
<P>
	By winning the French Open Sunday, Agassi became only the fifth  
man to complete a career Grand Slam. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
