<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Corn, Soybeans Rise; Wheat Falls / Board of Trade  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Wheat futures retreated , but corn and soybean  
futures edged higher Tuesday amid forecasts for rainfall that might 
relieve young crops stressed by the high temperatures in the 
Midwest. 
</P>
<P>
	Wheat for July delivery fell 2 1/2 cents to $2.55 1/4 a bushel on the  
Chicago Board of Trade; July corn rose 1/2 cent to $2.23 a bushel; 
July oats fell 3/4 cent to $1.25 3/4 a bushel; July soybeans rose 3/4 cent 
to $4.69 a bushel. 
</P>
<P>
	Beef futures finished mixed on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange,  
while pork futures fell sharply. 
</P>
<P>
	June live cattle rose 0.60 cent to 66.40 cents a pound; August  
feeder cattle fell 0.18 cent to 77.52 cents a pound; June lean hogs 
fell 0.82 cent to 51.10 cents a pound; July pork bellies fell the 
limit 3 cents to 49.62 cents a pound. 
</P>
</TEXT>
