<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia 4, Malta 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALONICA, Greece (AP)-- Savo Milosevic scored two goals Tuesday  
as Yugoslavia trounced Malta 4-1 for its third victory in Group 8 
of qualifying for the 2000 European Championship. 
</P>
<P>
	The war in Yugoslavia forced UEFA, Europe's soccer governing  
body, to change the site from Belgrade and move the game to 
Salonica. 
</P>
<P>
	The Yugoslavs pressed from the start, but it was Malta which  
surprisingly took the lead with Nicholas Salliba scoring off a pass 
from Chuks Nwoko. 
</P>
<P>
	The Yugoslavs kept testing goaltender Ernest Barry, who was  
unyielding, making a series of decisive saves. He also was helped 
twice by the crossbar. 
</P>
<P>
	But Predrag Mijatovic tied it off a centering pass from Jovan  
Stankovic in the 36th minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Three minutes into the second half, Milosevic gave Yugoslavia  
the lead, and Darko Kovacevic made it 3-1 with the game's most 
spectacular goal. Before sending the ball into the Maltese goal, he 
dribbled past two defenders and Barry. 
</P>
<P>
	Seconds before the end of the game, Milosevic made it 4-1.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
