<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Devil Rays Place Eiland on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- The Tampa Bay Devil Rays placed  
right-hander Dave Eiland on the disabled list Tuesday and recalled 
left-hander Norm Charlton from Triple-A Durham. 
</P>
<P>
	Eiland (0-2, 4.09 ERA) started Monday night's game at Atlanta,  
but left after three innings because of stiffness in his lower 
back. The 36-year-old Charlton (0-0, 4.50) made two relief 
appearances during an earlier stint with the Devil Rays from April 
24-29. 
</P>
<P>
	The Devil Rays also announced they had agreed to contract terms  
with four players selected in last week's baseball draft -- 
infielder Oginga Aaron, outfielder Glenn Katz and pitchers Chris 
Crawford and Matthew Dailey. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
