<HEADLINE> El Aynaoui Injured at Merano Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MERANO, Italy (AP) -- Second-seeded Youness El Aynaoui was forced  
out of the Merano Open during his first-round match Tuesday because 
of a knee injury. 
</P>
<P>
	The Moroccan was losing 7-5, 2-0 to Argentina's Martin Rodriguez  
when he retired. 
</P>
<P>
	Another player from Argentina, Guillermo Canas, outlasted  
fifth-seeded Karim Alami of Morocco through two successive 
tie-breakers and won 7-6 (7-3) and 7-6 (7-5). 
</P>
<P>
	The start of play in the clay-court tournament was delayed for  
about six hours by rain. 
</P>
<P>
	Top-seeded Dominik Hrbaty, a semifinalist last week at the  
French Open, was slated to play Tuesday night against clay-court 
specialist Alberto Berasategui. But the match was put off until 
Wednesday because of the rain. 
  	   	
